    {
      "section_id": "601",
      "section_title": "Test Methods",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "11-4-2REGULATION 11 HAZARDOUS POLLUTANTS BERYLLIUM ROCKET MOTOR FIRING"
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "100",
      "section_title": "GENERAL",
      "history": [],
      "text": [],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "101",
      "section_title": "Description",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "The purpose of this Rule is to control the emission to the atmosphere of beryllium from rocket motor firing."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "200",
      "section_title": "DEFINITIONS",
      "history": [],
      "text": [],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "201",
      "section_title": "Beryllium Propellant",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "Any propellant incorporating beryllium which undergoes combustion to provide rocket propulsion."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "202",
      "section_title": "Rocket Motor Test Site",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "Any plant or installation where static test firing of a beryllium rocket motor and/or the disposal of beryllium propellant is conducted."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "300",
      "section_title": "STANDARDS",
      "history": [],
      "text": [],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "301",
      "section_title": "Emissions From Test Sites",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "A person shall not emit combustion products from rocket motor test sites which cause time weighted atmospheric concentrations of beryllium to exceed 75 microgram minutes per m3 of air within the limits of 10 to 60 minutes, accumulated during any 2 consecutive weeks, in any area in which an effect adverse to public health could occur."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "302",
      "section_title": "Emissions From Closed Tanks",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "A person shall not emit beryllium propellant combustion products from a closed tank in excess of 2 g per hour and maximum of 10 g per day."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "400",
      "section_title": "ADMINISTRAT IVE REQUIREMENTS",
      "history": [],
      "text": [],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "401",
      "section_title": "Notification to APCO of Sampling or Emission Tests",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "The APCO shall be notified at least 30 days prior to an air sampling test or emission test required by Sections 11-4-301 and 11-4-302 in order to have the option to conduct or observe the test."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "402",
      "section_title": "Measuring and Sampling",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "A person responsible for the firing of a beryllium rocket motor subject to Section 11-4-301 shall measure ambient air concentrations during and after firing and shall continuously sample combustion product from a tank subject to Section 11-4-302 so that compliance with standards can be determined."
      ],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "600",
      "section_title": "MANUAL OF P ROCEDURES",
      "history": [],
      "text": [],
      "subsections": []
    },
    {
      "section_id": "601",
      "section_title": "Test Met hods",
      "history": [],
      "text": [
        "Test methods and procedures for air sampling test and emission tests required in Section 11-4-402 are specified in the Manual of Procedures, Volume VI, Section 4. (Amended March 17, 1982)"
      ],
      "subsections": []
    }
  ],
